==German==
===Etymology===
This term comes from southern Germany, a compound word created from "hinter" (behind) and "fotzig", which comes from "Fotze".  This is NOT the same vulgar word used in high German, but rather the southern German meaning of "face", "mouth" or "gob".  Therefore, the meaning is an adjective for someone who is not honest and forthright, but rather who is false and speaks badly of you or does things behind your back.

see http://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hinterfotzig for the German.